==Abstract==

This draft specifies a compatibility commitment format for post-quantum (PQC)
signatures that matches libdogecoin PQC commitment encoding.

Canonical commitments are encoded in script as:

<source>
Falcon-512:  OP_RETURN 0x24 "FLC1" <32-byte commitment>
Dilithium2:  OP_RETURN 0x24 "DIL2" <32-byte commitment>
</source>

Where commitment bytes are:

<source>
commitment32 = SHA256(public_key_bytes || signature_bytes)
</source>

==Compatibility==

This draft is intentionally policy-level and consensus-neutral. It provides
deterministic script encoding and parsing conventions for interop between
Dogecoin Core tooling and libdogecoin PQC workflows.
